Name: Baker Hughes Incorporated
Article: 8 : [u'\r\n         Venezuelan oil production may tumble 20% by the end of 2017\r\n    ']
Body: [u'Venezuela\u2019s proved oil reserves was estimated at 300.9 billion barrels at the end of 2015, according to BP\u2019s                                                                                                                                                                                                           BP, -0.82%                                                                                                                                                \xa0Statistical Revenue of World Energy June 2016. That\u2019s below Saudi Arabia\u2019s 266.6 billion and much less than the U.S.\u2019s 55 billion. ', u'But it cost Venezuela about $27.62 to produce a barrel of oil and natural gas in 2016, according to a story published by WSJ News Graphics last year, which cites data from Rystad Energy UCube. That ranks it as fourth in terms of major producers who pay the most to get the commodities out of the ground. ', u'And profits have been cut significantly in recent years. Prices for the global benchmark Brent crude                                                                                                                                                                                                           LCOK7, -1.28%                                                                                                                                                \xa0trade at around $55 a barrel, down by about half from a high of roughly $113 in June of 2014. West Texas Intermediate                                                                                                                                                                                                           US:CLJ7                                                                                                                                                \xa0trades close to $53 a barrel, down from about $106 almost three years ago.', u'Venezuela has only $10.5 billion in foreign reserves left for the rest of the year, it owes about $7.2 billion in outstanding debt payments, according to a CNN report published this week. Those figures suggest that nation could soon run out of cash.', u' Read: This country can\u2019t shake its inglorious ranking as most miserable ', u' In a Jan. 31 report, Fitch Ratings said that Petr\xf3leos de Venezuela S.A. faces a challenging year and that default for the state-owned oil and natural-gas company is \u201cprobable\u201d\u2014in part, due to \u201cmoderate\u201d oil price increase, lower production and a weak liquidity position.', u'Williams said many of the service companies won\u2019t do business with Venezuela or have scaled back their operations, such as Schlumberger Ltd.                                                                                                                                                                                                           SLB, -0.54%                                                                                                                                                \xa0and Halliburton Co.                                                                                                                                                                                                           HAL, -0.31%                                                                                                                                                ', u'In April of last year, Schlumberger said it would reduce activity in the country, partly because of \u201cinsufficient payments received in recent quarters.\u201d', u'For the record, however, that is still above the output of 1.972 million barrels a day it\u2019s supposed to target as a part of the OPEC-led production cut agreement that kicked in at the start of the year.', u' Data from Baker Hughes                                                                                                                                                                                                           BHI, +0.71%                                                                                                                                                 show Venezuela\u2019s oil rig count at 50 in January of this year, down from 71 in March of 2016. ']

Name: Coca-Cola Company (The)
Article: 10 : [u'\r\n         U.S. stocks open slightly higher; Nasdaq struggles for 3rd straight record\r\n    ']
Body: [u'U.S. stocks opened modestly higher on Thursday, with the Nasdaq inching toward its third-straight record, after a spate of strong earnings reports helped lift the broader market. The S&P 500 index                                                                                                                                                                                                           SPX, -0.21%                                                                                                                                                 gained two points, or 0.1%, to 2,296.63. The Dow Jones Industrial Average                                                                                                                                                                                                           DJIA, -0.33%                                                                                                                                                 climbed 26 points, or 0.1%, to 20,081. The Nasdaq Composite Index                                                                                                                                                                                                           COMP, -0.06%                                                                                                                                                 advanced three points, or 0.1%, to 5,686. Viacom Inc.                                                                                                                                                                                                           VIAB, +0.71%                                                                                                                                                 rose after beating earnings and revenue forecasts, while Coca-Cola                                                                                                                                                                                                           KO, -0.38%                                                                                                                                                 shares retreated after profits met expectations but its outlook fell short. CVS Health Corp.                                                                                                                                                                                                           CVS, -0.50%                                                                                                                                                 shares jumped after beating earnings and revenue forecasts. Dunkin\' Brands Group Inc.                                                                                                                                                                                                           DNKN, -0.04%                                                                                                                                                 rose after posting a fourth-quarter profit. Twitter Inc.                                                                                                                                                                                                           TWTR, +0.96%                                                                                                                                                 shares slipped after posting lackluster quarterly results.']
